## NOTE: n is number in *each* group
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;conclusion&quot;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Statistical A/B test or hypothesis test, is a very good technique to solve real world problem. However, understanding more about underlying assumption and requirement is important in real world. In statistical world, there is no “yes or no”, only good or bad.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Free Young</name></author><summary>These are all start from the moment when I saw the post: http://datapirates.blogspot.de/2016/03/why-ab-testing-sucks.html. It claims A/B test, which is exactly two-sample t test, is useless. Below is simulation running with R.</summary></entry></feed>
